cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SI 

The paper discusses evaluative bibliometrics, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are likely categories as they deal with the organization and retrieval of scientific literature. cs.CY (Computational Biology) is also a possibility as the study uses a dataset from F1000Prime, a post-publication peer review system of the biomedical literature. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are less likely but still possible categories as they may involve the evaluation of research impact and citation analysis.
